                "question": "What should people in long-term care facilities or group homes do?",
                "answerBody": "On April 24, the Health Department recommended that all health care personnel in long-term care facilities, correctional facilities, and other congregate settings where health care is provided wear face masks, regardless of the presence of COVID-19 in the facility.\n\nOn March 13, the Governor issued an executive order requiring nursing homes, assisted-living facilities and state therapeutic care residences to prohibit visitor access to reduce facility-based transmission. This prohibition does not apply to medically necessary personnel or visitors for residents receiving end of life care.\n\nThese resources are all available on our website at [www.healthvermont.gov/COVID19-longtermcare](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/long-term-care-and-group-living-settings) \n\n* Vermont Health Advisory: Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19) in Long-Term Care Facilities: [https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/HAN-LTCF-3-4-2020.pdf](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/HAN-LTCF-3-4-2020.pdf)  \n\n* CDC: Strategies to Prevent the Spread of COVID-19 in Long-Term Care Facilities: [https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/healthcare-facilities/prevent-spread-in-long-term-care-facilities.html](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/healthcare-facilities/prevent-spread-in-long-term-care-facilities.html) \n\n* CDC: Guidance for Retirement Communities and Independent Living:  [https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/community/retirement/index.html?deliveryName=USCDC_2067-DM23558](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/community/retirement/index.html?deliveryName=USCDC_2067-DM23558)\n\n* The Department of Disabilities, Aging and Independent Living also has additional info on its website: [https://dail.vermont.gov/novel-coronavirus-information](https://dail.vermont.gov/novel-coronavirus-information)\n\nSenior Centers and Adult Day programs have closed their programs in compliance with the Governor’s State of Emergency in Response to COVID-19. As of April 10, that executive order has been extended until May 15th. At which time the Governor, in consultation with the Vermont Department of Health and the Department of Public Safety/Division of Emergency Management shall assess the emergency and determine whether to amend or extend the State of Emergency.\n\n[https://dail.vermont.gov/sites/dail/files//documents/Adult_Day_and_Senior_Centers.pdf](https://dail.vermont.gov/sites/dail/files//documents/Adult_Day_and_Senior_Centers.pdf)\n\nHere are other useful resources:\n\n* PPE Availability Memo: [https://dail.vermont.gov/sites/dail/files//documents/supply_memo_to_DAIL_Providers_Local_EMD_Contacts_3-20-20.pdf](https://dail.vermont.gov/sites/dail/files//documents/supply_memo_to_DAIL_Providers_Local_EMD_Contacts_3-20-20.pdf) \n\n* LTC Screening Protocol: [https://dail.vermont.gov/sites/dail/files//documents/3%2015%2020%20Updated%20Screening%20Questions%20Guidance.pdf](https://dail.vermont.gov/sites/dail/files//documents/3%2015%2020%20Updated%20Screening%20Questions%20Guidance.pdf)",
                "date": "2020-04-27"
