                "answerBody": "No visitors are allowed in nursing homes, assisted-living facilities and state therapeutic care residences. Medically necessary personnel and visitors for residents receiving end-of-life care are allowed.\n\nThe Health Department recommends that all health care personnel in long-term care facilities, correctional facilities, and other congregate settings where health care is provided wear face masks, regardless of the presence of COVID-19 in the facility.\n\nAny new admissions to nursing homes, assisted living residences, and residential care homes must complete the full 14-day quarantine period first.\n\n[Senior Centers and Adult Day Programs](https://dail.vermont.gov/sites/dail/files//documents/Adult_Day_and_Senior_Centers.pdf) have closed their programs in\ncompliance with the Governor’s State of Emergency in Response to\nCOVID-19. The executive order has been extended until June 15. At which time the Governor, in consultation with the Vermont\nDepartment of Health and the Department of Public Safety/Division of\nEmergency Management shall assess the emergency and determine whether to\namend or extend the State of\nEmergency.\n\nFind guidance for [long-term care and group living](https://www.healthvermont.gov/COVID19-longtermcare)\n[settings](https://www.healthvermont.gov/COVID19-longtermcare).",
