                "question": "What do I do if I believe I had close contact with someone who has COVID-19?",
                "answerBody": "If you have been in close contact with a person who tested positive for COVID-19, monitor yourself for symptoms. This includes checking your temperature every day, watching for symptoms (fever, cough, and shortness of breath) and staying home. \n\nIf you develop symptoms of COVID-19 and are a close contact of someone who tested positive, you should: \n\n1. Call your health care provider and\n\n2. Call the Vermont Department of Health at 802-863-7240. \n\nIf you do not develop symptoms, you do not need to call the Health Department.\n\nRead [what to do if you're a close contact of someone with COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID-19_What-to-do-if-you-are-a-close-contact-of-someone-with-COVID-19_final.pdf).",
