            {
                "question": "What types of disinfectants should I be using to clean?",
                "answerBody": "Read the CDC's [Cleaning and Disinfection for Households](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/cleaning-disinfection.html) guidance.\n\nMake sure you are using cleaning products and disinfectants safely. Follow these guidelines:\n\n* Follow the directions on the label\n\n* Don’t mix chemicals\n\n* Wear protective gear (such as gloves)\n\n* Use them in a well-ventilated area\n\n* Store them out of reach of children\n\nIf you feel sick after using disinfectants, you can chat with the [New England Poison Control Center](https://www.nnepc.org/) on their website, call 1-800-222-1222 or text POISON to 85511.",
                "date": "2020-04-27"
            },
            {
                "question": "What types of disinfectants should I be using to clean?",
                "answerBody": "Read the CDC's [cleaning and disinfecting your home](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/disinfecting-your-home.html) guidance.\n\nMake sure you are using cleaning products and disinfectants safely. Follow these guidelines:\n\n* Follow the directions on the label\n\n* Don’t mix chemicals\n\n* Wear protective gear (such as gloves)\n\n* Use them in a well-ventilated area\n\n* Store them out of reach of children\n\nIf you feel sick after using disinfectants, you can chat with the [New England Poison Control Center](https://www.nnepc.org/) on their website, call 1-800-222-1222 or text POISON to 85511.",
                "date": "2020-04-28"
            },
            {
                "question": "What types of disinfectants should I be using to clean?",
                "answerBody": "Find tips from the CDC on how to [clean and disinfect your home](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/disinfecting-your-home.html) routinely and when someone is sick.\n\nMake sure you are using cleaning products and disinfectants safely. Follow these guidelines:\n\n*   Wear protective gear (such as gloves and eye protection)\n*   Use them in a well-ventilated area\n*   Follow the directions on the label\n*   Use no more than the amount recommended on the label\n*   Use water at room temperature for dilution (unless the label says a different temperature)\n*   Don’t mix chemicals\n*   Label diluted cleaning products\n*   Store them out of reach of children and pets\n\nYou should never eat, drink, breathe or inject these products into your body or apply directly to your skin as they can cause serious harm. Do not wipe or bathe pets with these products or any other products that are not approved for animal use.\n\nIf you feel sick after using disinfectants, you can chat with the [New England Poison Control Center](https://www.nnepc.org/) on their website, call 1-800-222-1222 or text POISON to 85511.",
                "date": "2020-08-20"
            }
        ],
