                "answerBody": "Usually, a health care provider collects samples (specimens) from you in one of two ways:\n\n1.  The health care provider collects a sample using a nasopharyngeal or NP swab. This is when a long, dry swab is inserted through one nostril and is rubbed against the back of your nose and throat.\n2.  The health care provider collects a sample using a nasal swab. This is when a short, dry swab is used to collect a sample from the front of your nose. This type of test is used at the Health Department’s [pop-up testing sites](https://www.healthvermont.gov/covid-19/testing/what-expect). It is also used for certain priority groups, including children.",
