                "answerBody": "Whatever your age, staying home is still the best way to lower our risk of COVID-19, but many of us are eager to take small steps to safely see our friends and family again. Learn more about [getting together with friends and family](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4690). \n\nEven though the risk for severe illness increases with age and is higher for older adults and people of any age with certain underlying medical conditions, young people can also get sick. The virus can spread even if a person does not have any symptoms. \n\nTaking these health and safety precautions protects everyone and helps slow the spread of this virus:\n\n*   Stay home if you are sick.\n*   Keep a 6-foot distance from people you don't live with.\n*   Wear a [face mask or covering](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID-19-VDH-mask-guidance.pdf) when you can't keep 6 feet apart.\n*   Avoid crowded indoor spaces.\n*   Wash your hands often.",
