                "question": "How can children socialize while still preventing the spread of COVID-19?",
                "answerBody": "As Vermont sees a significant surge of new COVID-19 cases across the state, Governor Scott’s [Executive Order](https://governor.vermont.gov/sites/scott/files/documents/ADDENDUM%208%20TO%20AMENDED%20AND%20RESTATED%20EXECUTIVE%20ORDER%2001-20.pdf) prohibits gathering with people from other households as of November 14, 2020. This includes both inside and outside social gatherings, and in public and private spaces. People who live alone may gather with members of their immediate family living in a different household.\n\nYou can prevent the spread of COVID-19 by following these general [prevention steps](https://www.healthvermont.gov/covid-19/protect-yourself-others/prevent-covid-19):\n\n*   Stay home if you are sick.\n*   Wash your hands often.\n*   Keep your social circle small.\n*   Stay at least 6 feet away from people you don't live with.\n*   Wear a mask (children over 2 who are able) when you’re outside and can’t keep 6 feet apart or anytime you’re inside with people you don’t live with.\n\nIf you are around other people, it’s safest to be outdoors. Because of the nature of how the virus spreads and how it survives, [being indoors increases your risk](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4746) of spreading or getting COVID-19. Sleepovers involve close contact and indoor spaces with people who are outside your household, so they are prohibited.\n\nThere will always be some risk of COVID-19 when we leave home, but it is possible to live your life and stay safer. Look for three things to help weigh the risk when making plans or going out:\n\n*   **6-Foot Spaces**: Can I easily keep 6 feet from others?\n*   **Masks on Faces**: Will people wear masks?\n*   **Uncrowded Places**: Is there enough space for people to spread out?\n\nImagine these things as layers protecting us from getting and spreading COVID-19. The more layers we have, the lower the risk. Find more [tips on preventing COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/staysafevt).\n\nChildren can also continue to take advantage of technology to play games or keep in touch with friends and family. These changes will continue to be difficult, but we are all doing our part to slow down this pandemic.\n\n**Learn more:**\n\n*   [Resources for families with children](https://www.healthvermont.gov/covid-19/your-community/families-children)\n*   [Coping with family stress during COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/covid-19/protect-yourself-others/coping-stress)\n*   [Face coverings for children](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID19-childfacecovering.pdf)",
                "date": "2020-11-16"
            }
