                "question": "How can I prepare at home?",
                "answerBody": "* **Plan ways to care for those in your home who might be at greater risk for serious complications,** like older adults (65 years and older) and people of any age who have underlying medical conditions. Make sure those who need regular medicine, medical supplies and equipment have what they need. \n\n* **Choose a room in your home that can be used to separate sick household members from those who are healthy.** Identify a separate bathroom for the sick person to use, if possible. Plan to clean these rooms, as needed, when someone is sick.\n\n* **Make sure you have enough groceries and other supplies for 14 days in case you get sick and need to quarantine.** Stock up on only what you will need for 14 days. Do not buy more than you will need so you can leave supplies for other people.\n\n* **Get support from others.** Talk with your neighbors about emergency planning. If your neighborhood has Front Porch Forum, consider joining to connect with neighbors, information and resources. Stay in touch by phone or email with family and friends, especially those who are 65 years and older, who have underlying medical conditions, or who live alone.\n\n* **Take care of the emotional health of your household members.** Outbreaks can be stressful for adults and children. Talk with your children about the outbreak, try to stay calm, and reassure them that they are safe.",
