                "question": "Does the Be Smart, Stay Safe Order mean I can be arrested or will need special papers if I leave my home?",
                "answerBody": "Enforcement of the Governor’s executive order extension  — [Be Smart, Stay Safe](https://governor.vermont.gov/sites/scott/files/documents/ADDENDUM%2014%20TO%20EXECUTIVE%20ORDER%2001-20.pdf) — will be mainly be done through education and voluntary compliance.\n\n* The Order does not close roads and does not establish roadblocks or checkpoints.\n\n* Motor vehicle and pedestrian traffic will continue as Vermonters do outdoor activities that are allowed and travel to and from businesses (including grocery stores and pharmacies) and other entities that are allowed to operate under the Order.\n\n* There will not be motor vehicle stops or people detained for questioning about their travel, but law enforcement officers may be reminding people of the Order if they see groups gathering or businesses operating in violation of the Order.\n\nRead the latest updates to the [Be Smart, Stay Safe Executive Order](http://governor.vermont.gov/document-types/executive-orders).",
