                "question": "Where can I go to get tested?",
                "answerBody": "The Vermont Department of Health announced expanded testing of Vermonters with COVID-19 symptoms. There are several testing sites and drive-through locations across the state and more may be added as the situations evolves. \n\n**Before you can be tested** you must have a referral from your health care provider. People who arrive at a testing site without a referral from their health care provider will not be tested.\n\nIf you are having symptoms of COVID-19 (cough, fever, shortness of breath), call your health care provider. If you are having a medical emergency, call 9-1-1 or go to the hospital. The [CDC Self Checker Tool](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/symptoms-testing/index.html) can help you review your symptoms. Read [what to do if you are sick](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/if-you-are-sick/index.html).",
                "date": "2020-04-27"
            }
