                "question": "Does smoking or vaping increase the risk of getting seriously ill from COVID-19?",
                "answerBody": "There is growing evidence that e-cigarette use or vaping can harm lung health. The coronavirus attacks the lungs, making it harder for people who smoke or vape – tobacco, cannabis or anything else – to fight off the virus, putting them at much greater risk of severe illness, even death.  \n\n802Quits is the Vermont tobacco quit resource. You can get help to quit by phone or online. \n\nBy phone, call **1-800-QUIT-NOW** for 1:1 coaching, available 24/7, with email and text support. \n\nOnline: [802Quits.org](https://802quits.org/) \n\nBy quitting, you’ll also protect people in your household by reducing their exposure to secondhand smoke and aerosol as you spend more time at home right now.",
