                "answerBody": "The number of people who have tested positive for COVID-19 by county is updated daily on the [Vermont Dashboard](https://www.healthvermont.gov/covid-19/current-activity/vermont-dashboard). \n\nThe number of Vermonters who have tested positive for COVID-19 by the town where they live is updated weekly on the [map of cases by town](https://www.healthvermont.gov/covid-19/current-activity/covid-19-communities). \n\nWhen looking at the county or town numbers, please remember that low or no recent cases is not the same as “safer.” We know the virus is in our communities, and we should continue to follow health guidance to slow the spread of COVID-19 – no matter where we live in or visit. The maps reflect the number of people who had a positive test. There may be people in your county or town that have COVID-19 but have not been tested. \n\n[Weekly Data Summaries](https://www.healthvermont.gov/covid-19/current-activity/weekly-data-summary) include more details on who has been impacted by COVID-19 in Vermont. You can find out more about testing trends, outbreaks, pre-existing conditions and symptoms of Vermonters with COVID-19.",
                "date": "2020-11-06"
            }
