                "question": "There are renters in local short-term rentals. Is that allowed?",
                "answerBody": "The Stay Home, Stay Safe Order makes clear that lodging facilities – which includes hotels, motels, bed and breakfasts, inns, short term rentals (for example, VRBO, Homeaway, Airbnb, etc.), and all public and private camping facilities and RV parks – are to be closed except for stated exemptions when supporting the state’s COVID-19 response. Additionally, the Governor has suspended online lodging reservations.\n\nUnder the Stay Home, Stay Safe Order, the Vermont State Police and local law enforcement will monitor lodging providers for compliance and work with the Attorney General’s Office on [additional compliance measures](http://ago.vermont.gov/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/AGO-EO-Enforcement-Directive-4.3.20.pdf), if needed.\n\nIf members of the public have concerns about lodging facilities that are violating the “Stay Home, Stay Safe” Executive Order, the Department of Public Safety has created an online [non-compliance complaint form](http://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=O5O0IK26PEOcAnDtzHVZxp8VoIcMV9NNu0QyG_vdGAVUN1pLSTdOMERRR1dXOVpZMDBZUEtNVlhXMi4u) to gather more information.\n\nRead the [Vermont State Police Guidance on enforcement](https://vsp.vermont.gov/covid19/stayhome_enforcement).",
