                "answerBody": "The Health Department encourages parents to follow State and CDC guidelines for travel and social distancing. Be sure to consider the health of each household, including if anyone in the homes has current symptoms of COVID-19 or has an underlying medical condition before moving a child between them.\n\nIf one of the parents has concerns and does not want to move children between households, we encourage parents to consult with their child’s pediatrician to discuss any possible health risks to the child.",
