                "question": "What should families do if they are not able to get formula, diapers, or other baby necessities?",
                "answerBody": "Families can call Help Me Grow-VT at 2-1-1 ext. 6 to be directed to services in their area that may be able to assist with formula, diapers, or other necessities. Any infant or child under age 5 that is on Medicaid or Dr. Dynasaur is considered income eligible for WIC (Women, Infants and Children). Food banks and food shelves may be resources for families not eligible for WIC. \n\nVermont WIC is open and most services are being done by phone appointment to align with social distancing efforts. Please visit the WIC website at [https://www.healthvermont.gov/family/wic](https://www.healthvermont.gov/family/wic) for the most accurate information about the program. Apply for WIC online or text VTWIC to 855-11. To connect with WIC in your area, visit [https://www.healthvermont.gov/local](https://www.healthvermont.gov/local).\n\nFind more [information and resources for families with children](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/resources).",
