            {
                "question": "Where can I get tested for COVID-19?",
                "answerBody": " *IMPORTANT: Everyone must have a referral from their health care provider in order to be tested.* \n\nThere are several testing sites and drive-through locations across the state and more may be added as the situations evolves.\n\nCall your health care provider first to be evaluated. Your health care provider will determine if you need a test. People who are NOT experiencing symptoms will not be tested. People who arrive at a testing site without a referral from their health care provider will not be tested.\n\nIf you are having [symptoms of COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/about-coronavirus-disease-covid-19), call your health care provider. If you are having a medical emergency, call 9-1-1 or go to the hospital. The [CDC Self Checker Tool](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/symptoms-testing/index.html) can help you review your symptoms. Read [what to do if you are sick](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/if-you-are-sick/index.html).",
