                "answerBody": " *IMPORTANT: Everyone must have a referral from their health care provider in order to be tested.* \n\nThere are several testing sites and drive-through locations across the state and more may be added as the situations evolves.\n\nIf you are having [symptoms of COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/about-coronavirus-disease-covid-19), call your health care provider to be tested. Health care providers are encouraged to order a test for any child or adult who is showing symptoms of COVID-19, even if their symptoms are mild.\n\nPeople who are NOT experiencing symptoms will not be tested. People who arrive at a testing site without a referral from their health care provider will not be tested.\n\nIf you are a health care worker, first responder, or child care provider, [learn how you can get tested](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/infectious-disease/novel-coronavirus-covid-19-health-care-professionals).\n\nIf you are having a medical emergency, call 9-1-1 or go to the hospital.\n\nFind out [what to do if you are sick](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/if-you-are-sick/index.html) from the CDC and [what to do while you’re waiting for test results](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/HS-ID-COVID19-Waiting-For-Test-Results-Handout.pdf).",
