                "answerBody": "If you are having [symptoms of COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/about-coronavirus-disease-covid-19), call your health care provider for a referral. Health care providers are encouraged to order a test for any child or adult who is showing symptoms of COVID-19, even if their symptoms are mild.\n\nThere are several testing sites and drive-through locations across the state and more may be added as the situation evolves. Any Vermonter without symptoms can be tested at a pop-up site without a doctor’s referral, but [registration for testing is required](https://humanresources.vermont.gov/popups). Regular test collection locations still require a doctor’s referral.\n\nThe following groups are encouraged to [get tested at pop-up sites](https://humanresources.vermont.gov/popups): health care workers, first responders (EMS, fire, and law enforcement), child care providers currently serving essential workers, and anyone in quarantine for 7 or more days (including people returning to Vermont from other states and countries). \n\nIf you are having a medical emergency, call 9-1-1 or go to the hospital.\n\nFind out [what to do if you are sick](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/if-you-are-sick/index.html) from the CDC and [what to do while you’re waiting for test results](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/HS-ID-COVID19-Waiting-For-Test-Results-Handout.pdf).",
