                "answerBody": " \n\n The Department of Public Safety and the Vermont State Police recommended to Vermont municipal leaders and law-enforcement executives that enforcement of the Governor’s Stay Home, Stay Safe Order be handled mainly through education and voluntary compliance.\n\nIf members of the public have concerns about businesses, lodging properties or restaurants that are violating the “Stay Home, Stay Safe” Executive Order, the Department of Public Safety has created an online [non-compliance complaint form](http://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=O5O0IK26PEOcAnDtzHVZxp8VoIcMV9NNu0QyG_vdGAVUN1pLSTdOMERRR1dXOVpZMDBZUEtNVlhXMi4u) to gather more information. For complaints regarding individuals who are failing to self-quarantine, as required, please call your local law-enforcement agency.\n\nRead the [Attorney General’s Enforcement Directive](http://ago.vermont.gov/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/AGO-EO-Enforcement-Directive-4.3.20.pdf). \n\nFind out more about [what the Stay Home/Stay Safe Order means to Vermonters](https://vem.vermont.gov/StayHome).",
