                "answerBody": "Long-term rental leases are allowed. Moving and moving services are also allowed, so long as social distancing guidelines are followed.\n\nReal estate services, including by real estate firms, brokerages, attorneys or individuals, must conduct as much work as possible remotely to minimize in-person contact. The Governor’s April 17 guidance on [Work Smart &amp; Stay Safe - Restart VT: Phase 1](http://governor.vermont.gov/content/addendum-10-executive-order-01-20) allows real estate and related services (such as title searches, appraisals, and home inspections), to begin limited operations again.\n\n* Real estate services must be limited to interactions of no more than two people (the professional and a client).\n\n* Real estate open houses should not occur, but scheduled property showings, where no more than two people are present, may occur.\n\n* Title searches should be conducted by appointment.\n\n* Appraisers should use drive-by appraisals as an alternative to entering a home if possible.\n\nMore housing information is available at the [ACCD’s COVID-19 Resource Recovery Center](http://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/individuals#individual-housing).",
