                "question": "Is there food available if I need it?",
                "answerBody": "The Vermont Foodbank and Vermont National Guard will give out free food to those in need at five different areas of Vermont beginning on April 22. People in need of food can go to these locations on the days and times listed below and receive a free, seven-day supply of ready-to-eat meals for each member of their household.\n\nPeople who are sick, have been asked to quarantine, or don’t have transportation can send a friend or relative to pick up meals for them. Those picking up food can come to the location nearest to them, open their trunk, and the food will be loaded by members of the Vermont National Guard.\n\nDates and locations (9:00 a.m. - 6:00 p.m. each day):\n\n* Wednesday, April 22 - Franklin County Airport (Highgate/Swanton)\n\n* Friday, April 24 - Rutland Southern VT Regional Airport (Clarendon)\n\n* Monday, April 27 - Hartness State Airport (Weathersfield/Springfield)\n\n* Tuesday, April 28 - William H Morse State Airport (Bennington)\n\n* Wednesday, April 29 - Northeast Kingdom International Airport (Coventry/Newport)\n\nThe need for these additional food resources is being considered on a week-by-week basis. Vermont food shelves are also able to meet the demand of clients and Vermont grocery stores are not experiencing shortages of most food items.\n\nVisit [Vermont Emergency Management](http://vem.vermont.gov/) for the latest news on food sites and more.\n\nVisit the [Vermont Foodbank](http://www.vtfoodbank.org/2020/03/covid-19-update.html) for more details on food resources during COVID-19 or to donate.",
