            {
                "question": "I don't have a house or a home, how can I stay safe?",
                "answerBody": "There is temporary housing available for people experiencing homelessness who are suspected to have or tested positive for COVID-19 and don’t require hospitalization. Call the Vermont Economic Services Division at 802-479-6151 Monday through Friday between 8:00 a.m. and 4:30 p.m. After hours, you can call 2-1-1.",
                "date": "2020-04-27"
            },
            {
                "question": "Is there temporary housing available if I might have or have tested positive for COVID-19?",
                "answerBody": "There is temporary housing available – commonly referred to as the motel voucher program – for people experiencing homelessness who are suspected to have or tested positive for COVID-19 and don’t require hospitalization.\n\nCall the [Vermont Economic Services Division](https://dcf.vermont.gov/esd/covid19) at 1-800-479-6151 Monday through Thursday from 8 a.m. to 6 p.m. and Friday from 8 a.m. to 4:15 p.m. After hours, you can call 2-1-1.\n\nIf you need to isolate or quarantine due to COVID-19 and don’t have a suitable home environment, there is temporary housing available. Learn more about [isolation/quarantine and recovery housing sites](https://humanservices.vermont.gov/help-and-resources/covid-19-information).",
                "date": "2020-10-19"
            }
        ],
