k themselves for symptoms by email, text or phone call. If symptoms are reported, a member of our team will reach out to provide guidance and next steps. Sara Alert helps our public health teams contain the spread of COVID-19. Please note, Sara Alert is not a contact tracing system. It is not GPS based, so it does not monitor your movements.\n\nAs the state reopens, Vermonters should consider keeping a contact journal – a list of other people who you have been in close contact with each day. If you do get sick, this would make it easier to get in touch with those people and so they can take proper precautions to prevent further spread of COVID-19.",
