                "question": "I am under a 14-day quarantine. Can I have the option to be tested and end my quarantine period?",
                "answerBody": "Anyone currently under quarantine who has had no symptoms during the first seven days of quarantine has the option to be tested at a [pop-up testing site](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/Pop-up-Testing-FAQs.pdf) without a doctor’s referral. Registration for testing is required.\n\nBased on data in the medical literature, the vast majority of people who are going to develop symptoms will do so by Day 7 or 8. For this reason, we offer what we consider to be a low-risk option for people to be tested at Day 7 or after in their quarantine and, if the test is negative, to end quarantine. This is simply an option, and it may not be practical or desirable for everyone.\n\nThe testing option is for:\n\n*   people returning to Vermont (for example, those who spend winter outside of Vermont, second homeowners and college students)\n*   visitors coming into Vermont\n*   close contacts of people who have tested positive\n\nFor anyone coming into Vermont, Day 0 is the day you arrive in Vermont.\n\nIf you live with someone who has tested positive for COVID-19 and they cannot completely isolate from you, then Day 0 is the day they are released from isolation. If they can isolate from you, then Day 0 is the last day you were in close contact with them.\n\nIf you are a close contact of someone who has tested positive for COVID-19 and you don’t live with them, then Day 0 is the last day you were in close contact with them.\n\nNew admissions to nursing homes, assisted living residences, and residential care homes must complete the full 14-day quarantine.\n\n**You can end your quarantine period before 14 days only if**:\n\n*   You have not had [symptoms](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/about-coronavirus-disease-covid-19) during your quarantine period;\n*   You are tested on Day 7 or later;\n*   You remain in quarantine until the result comes back; AND\n*   You receive a negative test result and are still not having symptoms.\n\nHowever, if you end your quarantine period before 14 days, you must continue to monitor yourself for symptoms for the full 14 days. If symptoms develop, you must isolate at home immediately and contact your health care provider.",
