rom the person who tested positive – for example, you live in the same home – Day 0 of your quarantine is the day they have ended their self-isolation.\n*   **If you are able to completely physically separate** – for example you do not live in the same home – Day 0 is the last time you were in close contact with them.\n*   In addition to getting tested at pop-up testing sites, you can also get tested through your health care provider, Federally Qualified Health Centers, commercial testing sites, and other testing sites as they come on board.\n*   If you develop symptoms at any point during your quarantine, contact your health care provider and the Health Department right away. If you do not have a health provider, call 2-1-1.\n*   You can [sign up to receive daily symptom check reminders](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/EpiInfoWebSurvey/Home/9c2e5941-1ba7-4ab4-84be-558ba7684f5d) with Sara Alert. If you report any symptoms of COVID-19 through Sara Alert, a member of the Health Department’s team will contact you with guidance and next steps.",
