minders](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/EpiInfoWebSurvey/Home/9c2e5941-1ba7-4ab4-84be-558ba7684f5d) with Sara Alert, a free, automated and secure reminder system to check for common COVID-19 symptoms. Sara Alert is not a contact tracing system. It is not GPS based, so it does not monitor your movements. If you report any symptoms of COVID-19 through Sara Alert, a member of the Health Department’s team will contact you with guidance and next steps.\n\n**\\*** For **close contacts** of people who have tested positive:\n\n*   **If you are NOT able to completely physically separate yourself** from the person who tested positive – for example, you live in the same home – Day 1 of your quarantine is the day after they have ended their self-isolation.\n*   **If you are able to completely physically separate** from the person who tested positive – for example you do not live in the same home – Day 1 of your quarantine is the day after the last time you were in close contact with them.\n*   In addition to getting tested at pop-up testing sites, you can also get tested through your health care provider, Federally Qualified Health Centers, commercial testing sites, and other testing sites as they come on board.",
