                "answerBody": "Check the Health Department’s webpage for [what to do if you are visiting or returning to Vermont](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/traveling-vermont). Get the latest travel and quarantine guidance, learn about testing options during quarantine, and find out how to safely connect with friends and family.\n\nStudents from [certain approved counties](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel) with low rates of active cases do not need to quarantine.\n\nAll students are strongly encouraged to [sign up with Sara Alert](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/EpiInfoWebSurvey/Home/9c2e5941-1ba7-4ab4-84be-558ba7684f5d) once arriving in Vermont to get two weeks of daily symptom check reminders.\n\nCollege students returning to Burlington can also use the city’s [Supportive Quarantine Pilot Program](https://www.burlingtonvt.gov/covid-19/quarantine). The program includes a move-in care package of fresh local goods, a mask, and hygiene supplies.\n\nColleges and universities must follow the [Mandatory Guidance for College and University Campus Learning](https://accd.vermont.gov/content/restart-plan-college-and-university-campus-learning). For specific questions about what you need to do, please contact your college or university.\n\nFind out [what happens at the Health Department when someone tests positive for COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID-19-Flowchart-When-Someone-Tests-Positive.pdf).",
