    {
        "id": 4705,
        "revisions": [
            {
                "question": "Can I get together with friends and family?",
                "answerBody": "Vermonters can leave home to get fresh air and exercise and for limited social interactions and gatherings of 25 or fewer people, preferably in outdoor settings, as long as health and safety precautions are taken. Learn how to [safely connect with friends and family](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/Safely_Connect_with_Friends_and_Family_FINAL.pdf).\n\nMembers of one household may choose to socialize – and allow children to play – with members of another trusted household, such as family, neighbors or friends. A trusted household is one that has taken seriously the importance of social distancing and proper hygiene in their day-to-day lives. By carefully limiting these closer social interactions at this time it will be easier to identify who else may have been exposed and need to self-isolate in case someone becomes sick.\n\nTo keep COVID-19 from spreading, we must continue to:\n\n* Stay home and away from others if you are sick with COVID-19, have recently been exposed to someone who has COVID-19, or just don’t feel well.\n* Keep a 6-foot distance from others when you meet people outside of your household.\n* Wash your hands frequently (hand sanitizer with at least 60% alcohol is acceptable when soap and water are not available).\n* Cough and sneeze into your elbow (even if you are wearing a cloth face mask or covering).\n* Wear a cloth face mask or covering over your nose and mouth.\n* Limiting travel to within Vermont to the extent possible and when you do travel, limit non-essential stops.\n\nOlder adults (age 65 and over), and people with underlying medical conditions, like heart and lung disease or diabetes, are more likely to develop severe illness. They should continue to stay home, and family and friends should do everything they can to help keep them safe.",
                "date": "2020-06-09"
            }
        ],
        "deletedDate": "2020-08-19"
    },
