                "question": "What is an antigen test?",
                "answerBody": "An antigen test is a newer type of COVID-19 test that identifies people who are currently infected with the COVID-19 virus.\n\nAntigen tests provide results much more quickly than diagnostic, or PCR, tests (the most common type of test used to diagnose COVID-19 infection). But antigen tests may not be as accurate.\n\nAntigen tests may be used to screen people to identify those who need a more definitive test.\n\nWe are monitoring how these antigen tests evolve and how results can best be used. Currently, people who test positive from antigen tests are not considered lab-confirmed cases and are not included in our total number of cases. However, we recommend they follow the same guidelines as a positive case to stay home (self-isolate). We would also conduct contact tracing and recommend a more accurate diagnostic test to confirm the positive result.\n\nAntigen tests are different from antibody (serologic) tests, which identify people who have previously been infected with the coronavirus and do not show whether a person is currently infected.",
