                "answerBody": "If you are a visitor and staying at a lodging, camping or short-term rental property in Vermont, you must [sign a Certificate of Compliance](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel/completing-the-lodging-certificate-of-compliance) certifying that you have met the quarantine requirement or have traveled from an [approved county with a low rate of active cases](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel).\n\nIn general, we rely on every visitor’s and every Vermonter’s voluntary compliance of the Governor’s orders to protect the health and safety of all. Vermonters and visitors are encouraged to take responsible common-sense measures in our daily lives to make sure we all are following CDC and Vermont Department of Health guidelines to prevent the spread of COVID-19.",
