        "id": 4730,
        "revisions": [
            {
                "question": "If I go on vacation, do I need to quarantine before I return to work?",
                "answerBody": "If you travel to an [approved county with a low rate of active infections](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel), you do not need to quarantine.\n\nIf you travel to a county that is not approved, then you need to quarantine for 14 days, either before you come back to Vermont or upon your return to Vermont. This applies to both employees living in Vermont and employees who live in a neighboring state and commute to Vermont for work.\n\nAnyone currently under quarantine who has had no symptoms during the first seven days of quarantine has the option to be tested with a PCR test. Find out how under “[I am under a 14-day quarantine. Can I have the option to be tested and end my quarantine period?](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4692)” on this page.\n\nYour employer may provide [sick or vacation time for you to complete your quarantine](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel/faqs#if-an-employee-travels-on-vacation-to-a-county-that-requires-quarantine-is-a-company-required-to-provide-vacation-or-sick-time-to-the-employee-to-complete-their-quarantine-upon-their-return).",
                "date": "2020-08-13"
            },
            {
                "question": "If I go on vacation, do I need to quarantine before I return to work?",
                "answerBody": "If you travel to an [approved county with a low rate of active infections](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel), you do not need to quarantine.\n\nIf you travel to a county that is not approved, then you need to quarantine for 14 days, either before you come back to Vermont or upon your return to Vermont. This applies to both employees living in Vermont and employees who live in a neighboring state and commute to Vermont for work.\n\nYou have the [option to get a PCR test on day 7](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4692) and end your quarantine with a negative test result. \n\nYour employer may provide [sick or vacation time for you to complete your quarantine](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel/faqs#if-an-employee-travels-on-vacation-to-a-county-that-requires-quarantine-is-a-company-required-to-provide-vacation-or-sick-time-to-the-employee-to-complete-their-quarantine-upon-their-return).",
                "date": "2020-09-03"
            },
            {
                "question": "If I go on vacation, do I need to quarantine before I return to work?",
                "answerBody": "If you travel to [certain counties with low rates of active cases](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel) (\"green\" counties), you do not need to quarantine. \n\nIf you travel to a “red” or “yellow” county, then you need to quarantine for 14 days, either before you come back to Vermont or upon your return to Vermont. This applies to both employees living in Vermont and employees who live in a neighboring state and commute to Vermont for work. \n\nIf you have not had [symptoms of COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/covid-19/symptoms-sickness/symptoms), you have the [option to get a PCR test on day 7](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4692) and end your quarantine with a negative test result. \n\nYour employer may provide [sick or vacation time for you to complete your quarantine](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel/faqs#if-an-employee-travels-on-vacation-to-a-county-that-requires-quarantine-is-a-company-required-to-provide-vacation-or-sick-time-to-the-employee-to-complete-their-quarantine-upon-their-return).\n\nFind more information on [returning to Vermont](https://www.healthvermont.gov/covid-19/travel-quarantine/vermonters-traveling-out-state).",
