        "revisions": [
            {
                "question": "I need to drop off someone at college. Do I need to quarantine?",
                "answerBody": "Yes. You have two options:\n\n1.  You follow the State of Vermont’s [travel and quarantine requirements](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel) OR  \n2.  You do the drop-off while under quarantine conditions.\n\nHere are the quarantine conditions for option 2:\n\n*   You must travel by personal vehicle to and from Vermont.\n*   Do not enter any college facilities. You may help the student unload at the curb only.\n*   Wear a face mask any time you are outside of your vehicle.\n*   Stay at least 6 feet away from people you don’t live with.  \n*   If your drive is farther than a single day trip, you may stay at a lodging property only if you quarantine at that property for your entire stay. This means you must stay in the room or house and not leave to go to the grocery store, restaurants or any other places where you might come into contact with other people. You may not use lodging property amenities such as pools, spas, gyms, recreation equipment or other general use facilities.\n\nWe strongly encourage you contact the school before you travel to find out if there are any move-in restrictions or rules.",
                "date": "2020-08-13"
            },
            {
                "question": "I need to drop off someone at college. Do I need to quarantine?",
