                "date": "2020-10-23"
            },
            {
                "question": "I need to pick up a student at college. Do I need to quarantine?",
                "answerBody": "Yes. If you are coming to Vermont to pick up a college student, you have two options:\n\n1.  You follow the State of Vermont’s [travel and quarantine requirements](https://www.healthvermont.gov/covid-19/travel-quarantine/visitors-vermont) OR\n2.  You do the pick-up while under quarantine conditions.\n\nHere are the quarantine conditions for option 2:\n\n*   You must travel by personal vehicle to and from Vermont.\n*   Do not enter any college facilities. You may help the student load at the curb only.\n*   Wear a face mask any time you are outside of your vehicle.\n*   Stay at least 6 feet away from people you don’t live with.\n*   If your drive is farther than a single day trip, you may overnight at a lodging property in a [“green” county](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel) only if you quarantine at that property for your entire stay. This means you must stay in the room or house and not leave to go to the grocery store, restaurants or any other places where you might come into contact with other people. You may not use lodging property amenities such as pools, spas, gyms, recreation equipment or other general use facilities.\n\n**If you are a Vermonter** picking up a student from an out-of-state college, you and the student will need to quarantine when you come back to Vermont for 14 days. If you have not had [symptoms of COVID-19](https://www.healthvermont.gov/covid-19/symptoms-sickness/symptoms), you have the [option to get a PCR test on day 7](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4692) and end your quarantine with a negative test result. \n\nCheck with the school before you travel to find out if there are any pick-up restrictions or rules.",
                "date": "2020-11-05"
            },
