                "question": "What does “infectious period” mean?",
                "answerBody": "The infectious period is the period of time where someone with COVID-19 has a high chance of spreading the virus to others. The infectious period starts two days before any symptoms began – or for people with COVID-19 who don't have symptoms, two days before they got tested – and continues [until they have recovered](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4601).\n\nPeople who had close interactions with the person with COVID-19 during this time are at risk and may be considered close contacts.",
