                "question": "Is it safe to travel for the holidays?",
                "answerBody": "As COVID-19 continues to spread both in Vermont and throughout the country, we all need to consider travel plans carefully as the holiday season approaches.\n\nTravel increases your chance of getting and spreading COVID-19. **Staying home is the best way to protect yourself and others.**\n\nRemember, the virus can spread easily among family and friends — because they are the ones we are often in close contact with — when they don’t know they have it. Like other aspects of our lives, this holiday season will look different and we need to do everything we can to keep each other safe.\n\nIf you are thinking about travel, take these steps:\n\n1.  [Check the map](https://dfr.vermont.gov/about-us/covid-19/modeling/covid-19-modeling-graphics) to find out the risk of COVID-19 infection at your destination.\n2.  [Decide if the risk](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/daily-life-coping/deciding-to-go-out.html#risk-going-out) is worth it for your family.\n3.  [Plan to have a safe trip](https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/travelers/travel-risk.html), remain flexible and get your [flu shot](https://www.healthvermont.gov/immunizations-infectious-disease/influenza/prevention).\n4.  [Quarantine](https://www.healthvermont.gov/response/coronavirus-covid-19/traveling-vermont) when you return.\n\nIf people are visiting you, they will need to quarantine at the place they are staying for 14 days. (They have the [option to get a PCR test on day 7](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4692) and end their quarantine with a negative test result). If you are hosting them, you don’t also need to quarantine, but you’ll need to make sure there is a [separate space](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4704https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/) for the people in quarantine.\n\nBe sure to talk to the people you plan to visit or who are visiting you about your comfort level with [COVID-19 prevention steps](https://www.healthvermont.gov/staysafevt).\n\nCelebrating holidays within your own household or sharing a meal virtually will not be the same as we’re used to, but we need to keep our guard up and continue to do all we can to keep from getting or spreading COVID-19.",
