                "question": "What is isolation?",
                "answerBody": "Isolation is when people with COVID-19 stay home, and away from other people, [until they have recovered](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4601), to prevent further spread. Learn about the timeline for people with COVID-19 ([with symptoms](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/images/2020/10/COVID19-timeline-with-symptoms.png) and [without symptoms](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/images/2020/10/COVID19-timeline-without-symptoms.png)) from being exposed to being released from isolation. \n\nIf you test positive for COVID-19, the Health Department's team of expert contact tracers will call you to provide guidance and information on staying home. They will also ask you about your [close contacts](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4575). Contact tracers call your close contacts to make sure they know to [stay home and quarantine](https://apps-test.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/index.html#4618) to prevent further spread. Learn more about the [timeline for close contacts,](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/images/2020/10/COVID19-timeline-close-contacts.png) from when they have may have been exposed, to when they can end quarantine.\n\nLearn more about [isolation, quarantine and self-observation](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID-19-chart-observation-isolation-quarantine_final.pdf) and [what to do if you have COVID-19.](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID-19_What-to-do-if-you-are-diagnosed-with-COVID-19_final.pdf)",
                "date": "2020-11-02"
