                "question": "What does my college student need to do when they come home to Vermont?",
                "answerBody": "Students attending an out-of-state college and anyone who [picks them up at college](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4731) will need to quarantine for 14 days when they come home to Vermont.\n\nQuarantine means that you need to stay home and apart from the people you live with for 14 days. You will need to:\n\n*   Stay at least 6 feet from people you live with,\n*   Wear a mask in common spaces,\n*   Use a separate bathroom,\n*   Eat separately, and\n*   Otherwise not be in close contact with the people you live with.\n\nIf you have not had symptoms of COVID-19, you have the [option to get a PCR test on day 7](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4692) and end your quarantine with a negative test result.\n\nWe understand that this will be difficult when you share a home with others, especially during the Thanksgiving holiday. But it is extremely important to stay in and complete quarantine to help keep from spreading the virus when you may not know you have it.\n\nFor the **people who are living with someone who is under quarantine**, you do not also need to quarantine. That means you can go to school, work, or the grocery store. However, you need to stay at least 6 feet from the people who are under quarantine. Be sure to disinfect commonly touched surfaces, and check yourself for symptoms for 14 days.\n\nLearn more about [quarantine](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4618) and tips about [quarantining when you share a home](https://www.healthvermont.gov/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/COVID-19_Prevention-Extended-Families-English.pdf).",
