                "question": "Can I come to Vermont to ski?",
                "answerBody": "Vermont ski areas will open for the 2021-21 ski season under [mandatory health and safety guidelines](https://accd.vermont.gov/content/vermont-ski-resort-covid-19-winter-operations-guidance), which include limits on lift and lodge capacities. If you come to Vermont to ski, you must follow attest that you completed Vermont’s quarantine requirements. \n\nThat means you must [quarantine](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4618) for 14 days before coming to Vermont. If you have not had symptoms of COVID-19, you have the [option to get a PCR test on day 7](https://apps.health.vermont.gov/COVID/faq/#4692) and end your quarantine with a negative test result. You must remain in quarantine until you travel to Vermont. \n\nIf you are coming from [certain counties with low rates of active cases](https://accd.vermont.gov/covid-19/restart/cross-state-travel) (“green” counties), you do not need to quarantine.\n\nYou will also be required to give your contact information to the ski resort in case contact tracing is needed.\n\nYou are required to wear a mask when you are in a lodge or anytime you can’t stay at least 6 feet away from people you don’t live with. Try to avoid crowded places as much as possible and stay at least 6 feet away from people you didn’t travel with.\n\nBe sure to check with the ski resort before you plan your trip to find out any other rules that the resort has.",
